    "body": "Related: vim/vim#20231\nCloses #39819\n\n## Problem\n\nThis follows the recent `fnamemodify(..., ':h')` root handling work, but Windows UNC paths have a separate root rule: the server/share pair is the root.\n\n`fnamemodify(..., ':h')` can treat the share name as an ordinary path component and strip `//foo/C$` back to `//foo`.\n\n## Solution\n\nPreserve basic Windows UNC share roots when computing the head.\n",
    "closed_at": null,
